Dataset Structure¶

The data contians the same images in 3 seperate forms:

1.) Color:     No changes have been these images as far as I am aware besides perhaps some croping or resizing.

2.) GreyScale: The grayscaled verison of the coloured images.

3.) Segmented: The coloured images with the background removed. and replaced with black

Under each folder (Color,Greyscale and segmented) the images are divided in subfolders based on there classification of the image classifactions as {plant_spieces}__{disease}. (apple__scab, potato__blight, blueberry__healthy, etc.)

In [361]:
# Initialize sums
mean = 0.
std = 0.
nb_samples = 0

for data, _ in tqdm(train_dataloader):
    batch_samples = data.size(0)  # batch size
    data = data.view(batch_samples, data.size(1), -1)  # (B, C, H*W)
    mean += data.mean(2).sum(0)
    std += data.std(2).sum(0)
    nb_samples += batch_samples

mean /= nb_samples
std /= nb_samples

print("Mean:", mean)
print("Std:", std)
# Mean: tensor([0.4663, 0.4889, 0.4103])
# Std: tensor([0.1762, 0.1500, 0.1927])

Training model¶

In [9]:
class PlantVillageModule(L.LightningModule):
    def __init__(self, model, model_hparams, optimizer_hparams):
        super().__init__()

        # Exports the hyperparameters to a YAML file, and create "self.hparams" namespace
        self.save_hyperparameters()  
        self.model = model
        for param in self.model.parameters(): 
            param.requires_grad = False
        for param in self.model.get_classifier().parameters():
            param.requires_grad = True
        
        self.loss_module = nn.CrossEntropyLoss()
        self.example_input_array = torch.zeros((1, 3, 224, 224), dtype=torch.float32) 

    def forward(self, imgs):
        return self.model(imgs)

    def configure_optimizers(self):

        optimizer = optim.AdamW(self.model.get_classifier().parameters(), **self.hparams.optimizer_hparams)

        scheduler = optim.lr_scheduler.MultiStepLR(optimizer, milestones=[100, 150], gamma=0.1)
        return [optimizer], [scheduler]

    def training_step(self, batch, batch_idx):

         

    def validation_step(self, batch, batch_idx):
        imgs, labels = batch
        preds = self.model(imgs)
        pred_labels = preds.argmax(dim=-1)
        acc = (labels == pred_labels).float().mean()
        loss = self.loss_module(preds, labels)
        
        self.log("val_acc", acc, prog_bar=True)
        self.log("val_loss", loss, prog_bar=True)
        return {"val_loss": loss, "val_acc": acc}
    
    def test_step(self, batch, batch_idx):
        imgs, labels = batch
        preds = self.model(imgs)
        pred_labels = preds.argmax(dim=-1)
        acc = (labels == pred_labels).float().mean()
        loss = self.loss_module(preds, labels)
        
        self.log("test_acc", acc, prog_bar=True)
        self.log("test_loss", loss, prog_bar=True)
        return {"test_loss": loss, "test_acc": acc}

        
    def val_epoch_end(self, outputs):
        avg_loss = torch.stack([x["test_loss"] for x in outputs]).mean()
        avg_acc = torch.stack([x["test_acc"] for x in outputs]).mean()

        self.log("val_loss_epoch", avg_loss, prog_bar=True)
        self.log("val_acc_epoch", avg_acc, prog_bar=True)

def train_model(model,epochs=2,logger_name='CsvLogger' , save_name='resnet', **kwargs):

    # Create a PyTorch Lightning trainer with the generation callback
    trainer = L.Trainer(
        logger = CSVLogger("logs", name=logger_name),
        default_root_dir=os.path.join(CHECKPOINT_PATH, save_name),  # Where to save models
        # We run on a single GPU (if possible)
        accelerator="auto",
        devices=1,
        # How many epochs to train for if no patience is set
        max_epochs=epochs,
        callbacks=[
            ModelCheckpoint(
                save_weights_only=True, mode="min", monitor="val_loss"
            ),  # Save the best checkpoint based on the maximum val_acc recorded. Saves only weights and not optimizer
            LearningRateMonitor("epoch"), # Log learning rate every epoch
            EarlyStopping(monitor="val_loss", mode="min",patience=5, verbose=True),
        ],  # stop early if test acc
    )  # In case your notebook crashes due to the progress bar, consider increasing the refresh rate


    print("No checkpoint found")
    lightning_model = PlantVillageModule(model, **kwargs)
    trainer.fit(lightning_model, train_dataloader, val_dataloader)
    lightning_model = PlantVillageModule.load_from_checkpoint(
        trainer.checkpoint_callback.best_model_path
    )  # Load best checkpoint after training

    # Test best model on validation and test set
    val_result = trainer.test(lightning_model, dataloaders=val_dataloader , verbose=False)
    test_result = trainer.test(lightning_model, dataloaders=test_dataloader , verbose=False)
    result = {"test": test_result[0]["test_acc"], "val": val_result[0]["test_acc"]}

    return model, result

In [17]:
def classifier(model,test_data):
    all_preds = []
    all_labels = []
    
    with torch.no_grad():
        for imgs, labels in tqdm(test_loader, desc="Evaluating"):
            imgs, labels = imgs.to(device), labels.to(device)
            outputs = model(imgs)
            preds = outputs.argmax(dim=1)
    
            all_preds.append(preds.cpu())
            all_labels.append(labels.cpu())
    
    all_preds = torch.cat(all_preds)
    all_labels = torch.cat(all_labels)

    return all_preds, all_labels
In [19]:
def generateConfustionMatrix(pred,labels,class_names):
    cm = confusion_matrix(labels, pred)

    plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))
    sns.heatmap(cm, annot=False, fmt="d", cmap="plasma", 
            xticklabels=class_names, yticklabels=class_names,
            annot_kws={"size": 6})
    plt.xticks(rotation=90) 
    plt.xlabel("Predicted")
    plt.ylabel("Actual")
    plt.title("Confusion Matrix")
    plt.show()
In [21]:
def generateConfusionMatrix_norm(pred, labels, class_names):
    cm = confusion_matrix(labels, pred)

    cm_normalized = cm.astype("float") / cm.sum(axis=1, keepdims=True)

    plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))
    sns.heatmap(cm_normalized, annot=False, fmt="d%", cmap="plasma",
                xticklabels=class_names, yticklabels=class_names)
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.xlabel("Predicted")
    plt.ylabel("Actual")
    plt.title("Normalized Confusion Matrix (Percentage)")
    plt.show()
